WorldStage Newsonline–  Niger Insurance Plc, a Nigerian firm which is into underwriting of life and general insurance business has authorized its directors  to restructure the company’s General Insurance Business and Life Insurance Business as a separate legal entity. These were part of the decisions made at its 50th Annual General Meeting (AGM) on January 20, 2021 at Peninsula Hotel, Lekki. The meeting also received the Report of the Directors, the Audited Financial Statements for the year ended December 31, 2019 and the respective Reports of the Auditors and Audit Committee Thereon There was also the re-election of Directors with Mr. Ebi Enaholo and Mrs. Olufemi Owopetu re-elected by rotation as Directors to the Company.